result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI 10th [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.20-.249)] and Operating w/ PAC 10th [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.20-.249)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI 10th [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.20-.249)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC 10th [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.20-.249)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Scott J. Aubry was found guilty of OWI 10th [Modifiers: Modifier-Alcohol Conc. (.20-.249)], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job.
